PHASE-2:
2. Install Required Jenkins Plugins Go to Manage Jenkins -> Plugins -> Available plugins, and install:
Pipeline (usually installed by default)
GitHub Integration Plugin
NodeJS Plugin (to build our sample app)

Credentials Binding Plugin
3. Configure NodeJS in Jenkins Go to Manage Jenkins -> Tools. Scroll down to NodeJS installations, click Add NodeJS, name it Node18, select version 18.x, and save.

Important:
The tool name configured in Jenkins must EXACTLY match the name used inside the Jenkinsfile.
Example:
If Jenkins Tool Configuration uses:
Node18
Then the Jenkinsfile must also use:
nodejs 'Node18'
Even a small mismatch like "node-18" vs "Node18" will cause the pipeline to fail.

