Phase 6: Debugging Tips
"No such DSL method" Error: This usually means you are using syntax for a plugin that isn't installed. Double-check your plugin manager.
Webhook Not Triggering: Go to GitHub Webhook settings and look at the Recent Deliveries tab at the bottom. It will show you exactly what HTTP error Jenkins returned (e.g., 403 Forbidden means Jenkins security is blocking it, or a 500/timeout means Jenkins is unreachable).
Pipeline Syntax Generator: If you are unsure how to write a step (like calling an AWS API or checking out code), use the Jenkins Snippet Generator. Click Pipeline Syntax on the left menu of your job. Select a step from the dropdown, fill out the UI, and it will generate the exact Groovy code for your Jenkinsfile.
Replay Feature: If a pipeline fails, don't trigger a whole new build. Click on the failed build and click Replay. You can edit the Jenkinsfile script directly in the UI just for that run to quickly test a fix without committing to Git.
